    "verification_notes": "dl_011 corrected: 'Kakati asenya' was ambiguous. 'Asenya' means to grind or gnash teeth, not to brush them. The correct full phrase for brushing teeth is 'asenya amannyo' (she brushes/scrubs her teeth). Added 'amannyo' to make meaning clear and accurate. All other entries verified clean."
